Description: CVE-2026-34197 - Prevent VM/Http transport abuse via BrokerView JMX
 Multiple security fixes for ActiveMQ BrokerView to prevent abuse of
 VM transport, validate nested composite URIs, and deny Http discovery
 transport in JMX context. An authenticated attacker could invoke
 BrokerView MBean operations with crafted discovery URIs exploiting
 the VM transport's brokerConfig parameter to load remote Spring XML
 contexts, enabling arbitrary code execution.
 .
 Combined backport of 3 upstream commits to 5.17.6:
  - 0ce7560ca: Prevent VM transport from being used with BrokerView
  - 9bb9ee6fd: Validate nested composite URIs used with BrokerView
  - 165c0db44: Add Http discovery transport to denied list for JMX
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/apache/activemq/commit/0ce7560ca5543d8c0213a23748ae70fc6ec360e8
Author: cshannon
Last-Update: 2026-04-17

